Four men are to spend seven years each behind the bars following their conviction by an Ekiti State High Court sitting in Ado Ekiti for alleged stealing and burglary. The accused persons: Owoeye Ojo, Agbetuyi Taiwo, Adeniyi Busayo and Lasisi Friday were convicted Justice Bamidele Omotoso for allegedly breaking into shop and stealing. The defendants were found guilty of the offence of burglary and stealing, due to their confessional statement and witnesses called during the trial. Arriving at the judgment, the court, which declined giving the convicts an option of fine, however, did not find them guilty of conspiracy which they were also charged with. The prosecution counsel, Mr Wale Fapohunda, had earlier said that the convicts committed the offences on August 26, 2017 at Enu Odi, Odo-Ado in Ado-Ekiti. Fapounda added that the defendants broke into the shop of one Mrs Iyabo Ige around 2am and 5am and carted away the following items, packs of noodles, cigarettes, tins of milk and packs of battery. He said that the offences contravened Sections 413 and 516 of the Criminal Code, Laws of Ekiti, 2012. The prosecution called three witnesses and tendered exhibits including pictures, stolen items and statements of the convicts. Mr Yinka Opaleye who is the defence counsel called only a witness in the course of the trial pleaded for leniency, praying the court to tamper justice with mercy as they were first offenders. But Justice Omotoso held that the prosecution has proved the case beyond the reasonable doubt saying that the court had no option than to sentence the convicts on the strength of evidence before it. 